From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Community <community@armbian.com>
Date: Mon, 5 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm: mach-sunxi: Enable GPU power domain for H616/H618

This patch writes to the PRCM register (0x7010254) to enable
the GPU power domain on Allwinner H616/H618 SoCs. Without this,
the Mali G31 GPU (Panfrost) cannot probe correctly.

The GPU power domain is controlled via bit 0 of the PRCM power
domain register. Writing 0 enables the power domain.

Tested on Walnut Pi Zero W (H618) and Orange Pi Zero 2W.

Signed-off-by: Community <community@armbian.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-sunxi/clock_sun50i_h6.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-sunxi/clock_sun50i_h6.c b/arch/arm/mach-sunxi/clock_sun50i_h6.c
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-sunxi/clock_sun50i_h6.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-sunxi/clock_sun50i_h6.c
@@ -XX,6 +XX,9 @@ void clock_init_uart(void)
 void clock_init(void)
 {
 	gpio_init();
+
+	/* Enable GPU power domain for H616/H618 */
+	writel(0, 0x07010254);  /* PRCM_GPU_PWROFF_GATING_REG */
+
 #if CONFIG_CONS_INDEX < 5
 	clock_init_uart();
 #endif
